segment.source: Important
segment.target: Important

segment.source: The Sync Your Settings feature in Windows 8 must be disabled to allow UE-V to function properly.
segment.target: The Sync Your Settings feature in Windows 8 must be disabled to allow UE-V to function properly.

segment.source: Synchronization of settings with both Windows 8 and UE-V will result in unpredictable synchronization behavior.

segment.source: Requirements for the Offline Files feature
segment.target: Requirements for the Offline Files feature

segment.source: The UE-V agent can synchronize user settings for computers that are not always connected to the enterprise network, such as a laptop computer or computers that are located at remote offices, as well as computers that are always connected to the enterprise network, such as Windows Servers that host virtual desktop interface (VDI) sessions.
segment.target: The UE-V agent can synchronize user settings for computers that are not always connected to the enterprise network, such as a laptop computer or computers that are located at remote offices, as well as computers that are always connected to the enterprise network, such as Windows Servers that host virtual desktop interface (VDI) sessions.

segment.source: The UE-V default configuration uses the Windows Offline File feature to synchronize settings.
segment.target: The UE-V default configuration uses the Windows Offline File feature to synchronize settings.

segment.source: Offline Files ensures that the user’s settings are available even when the computer leaves the enterprise network.
segment.target: Offline Files ensures that the user’s settings are available even when the computer leaves the enterprise network.

segment.source: Any changes that are made to settings are automatically synchronized with the settings storage location when the connection to the enterprise network is reestablished.
segment.target: Any changes that are made to settings are automatically synchronized with the settings storage location when the connection to the enterprise network is reestablished.

segment.source: Offline Files also ensures that the user’s settings are available for computers that are located in a remote office with a slow or limited connection.
segment.target: Offline Files also ensures that the user’s settings are available for computers that are located in a remote office with a slow or limited connection.

segment.source: To synchronize settings for computers that occasionally leave the enterprise network, the Offline Files feature must be enabled and started before the UE-V agent deployment begins.
segment.target: To synchronize settings for computers that occasionally leave the enterprise network, the Offline Files feature must be enabled and started before the UE-V agent deployment begins.

segment.source: The Offline Files feature is enabled by default on Windows 7.
segment.target: The Offline Files feature is enabled by default on Windows 7.

segment.source: The feature is disabled by default on Windows Server 2008 R2, Windows Server 2012, and Windows 8.
segment.target: The feature is disabled by default on Windows Server 2008 R2, Windows Server 2012, and Windows 8.

segment.source: If the Offline Files feature is not enabled, then UE-V settings synchronization will fail.
segment.target: If the Offline Files feature is not enabled, then UE-V settings synchronization will fail.

segment.source: Synchronization for computers with always-available connections
segment.target: Synchronization for computers with always-available connections

segment.source: When you use UE-V on computers that are always connected to the enterprise network, such as a Windows Server computer that hosts VDI sessions, then Offline Files should be disabled.
segment.target: When you use UE-V on computers that are always connected to the enterprise network, such as a Windows Server computer that hosts VDI sessions, then Offline Files should be disabled.

segment.source: When the UE-V agent is configured to synchronize settings without using Offline Files, the settings storage server is treated as a standard network share.
segment.target: When the UE-V agent is configured to synchronize settings without using Offline Files, the settings storage server is treated as a standard network share.

segment.source: Settings are synchronized when the network is available.
segment.target: Settings are synchronized when the network is available.

segment.source: In this configuration the UE-V agent can be configured to give a notification if the import of the application settings is delayed.
segment.target: In this configuration the UE-V agent can be configured to give a notification if the import of the application settings is delayed.

segment.source: If the Offline Files feature will not be used, you must disable the UE-V default behavior before or during the UE-V agent deployment.
segment.target: If the Offline Files feature will not be used, you must disable the UE-V default behavior before or during the UE-V agent deployment.

segment.source: To disable Offline Files for UE-V, do one of the following:
segment.target: To disable Offline Files for UE-V, do one of the following:

segment.source: Before you deploy the UE-V agent, mark the “Do not use Offline Files” checkbox in the UE-V Group Policy setting.
segment.target: Before you deploy the UE-V agent, mark the “Do not use Offline Files” checkbox in the UE-V Group Policy setting.

segment.source: During UE-V installation, set the AgentSetup.exe parameter at the command prompt or in a batch file.
segment.target: During UE-V installation, set the AgentSetup.exe parameter at the command prompt or in a batch file.

segment.source: For more information about how to deploy the agent, see Deploying the UE-V Agent.
segment.target: For more information about how to deploy the agent, see Deploying the UE-V Agent.

segment.source: If you disable the Offline Files setting for UE-V and you do not specify the SyncMethod parameter at the installation time, the UE-V agent installation will fail.
segment.target: If you disable the Offline Files setting for UE-V and you do not specify the SyncMethod parameter at the installation time, the UE-V agent installation will fail.

segment.source: You can also disable the Offline Files with PowerShell or WMI.
segment.target: You can also disable the Offline Files with PowerShell or WMI.

segment.source: For more information about WMI and PowerShell commands, see Managing the UE-V 1.0 Agent and Packages with PowerShell and WMI.
segment.target: For more information about WMI and PowerShell commands, see Managing the UE-V 1.0 Agent and Packages with PowerShell and WMI.

segment.source: Prerequisites for UE-V Generator support
segment.target: Prerequisites for UE-V Generator support

segment.source: Install the UE-V Generator on the computer that is used to create custom settings location templates.
segment.target: Install the UE-V Generator on the computer that is used to create custom settings location templates.

segment.source: This computer should have those applications installed whose settings will roam.
segment.target: This computer should have those applications installed whose settings will roam.

segment.source: You must be a member of the Administrators group on the computer that runs the UE-V Generator software.
segment.target: You must be a member of the Administrators group on the computer that runs the UE-V Generator software.

segment.source: Additionally, the UE-V Generator must be installed on a computer that uses an NTFS file system.
segment.target: Additionally, the UE-V Generator must be installed on a computer that uses an NTFS file system.

segment.source: The UE-V Generator software requires .NET Framework version 4.
segment.target: The UE-V Generator software requires .NET Framework version 4.
